      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auto-reply): surface model timeout failures once",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nTelegram/direct turns that fail with `LLM idle timeout (...): no response from model` currently fall through to the generic external-run failure copy (`Something went wrong... use /new`). In practice this can make a transient provider/model timeout look like a broken session and can contribute to noisy failure surfacing around terminal error delivery.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis keeps transient provider/model timeouts in the normal reply-delivery path: users see explicit timeout copy, while the reply operation remains active until the final visible failure payload is dispatched.\n\nThe branch has also been merged forward to current `main` in `1c8db06c28332a6082b076623a29cdaecee23aa8`, resolving the only update conflict in `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.ts` by preserving both the timeout-specific visible-failure retention and the newer restart-abort recovery behavior from `main`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers get clearer timeout guidance and should see less noisy failure surfacing around a single terminal model timeout. The change is limited to external-run/model-timeout failure handling and its regression coverage.\n\n## Evidence\n\nOriginal behavior proof:\n\n- Mantis Telegram Desktop proof captured before/after GIFs showing the PR adds a visible model-timeout reply in Telegram: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/95742#issuecomment-4781903128\n\nLocal verification after merging current `main` into the PR branch at `1c8db06c28332a6082b076623a29cdaecee23aa8`:\n\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.ts` passed.\n- `node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts src/gateway/server.cron.test.ts` passed:\n  - `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts`: 207 tests passed.\n  - `src/gateway/server.cron.test.ts`: 36 tests passed across the selected gateway shards, covering the previously red `checks-node-compact-small-7` area.\n- Targeted oxlint on the changed auto-reply files passed with 0 warnings / 0 errors.\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --noEmit` passed.\n\n## AI Assistance\n\nAI-assisted PR: authored with OpenClaw and GitHub Copilot-backed review requested.\n\nI understand what the code changes: timeout errors get specific user-visible copy, and failed reply operations are retained until final delivery completion instead of being cleared immediately.\n",
